# Remember to never publicly share your keystore.
# See https://flutter.dev/to/reference-keystore
key.properties
**/*.keystore
**/*.jks
# …except Séance's committed release keystore — deliberately public. It gives
# every build (local or CI) the SAME signing identity, so a downloaded release
# APK upgrades an installed one instead of demanding an uninstall (which would
# wipe the app's local data). The tradeoff, made knowingly: the signature
# provides upgrade continuity, NOT publisher authenticity — trust comes from
# downloading via this repo's releases (see build.gradle.kts).
!app/ci-release.jks
